==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Convoy pennant
<hw>Con"voy pen"nant</hw>. <def>A white pennant with red border,
carried: <it>(a)</it> Forward on all vessels on convoy duty.
<it>(b)</it> Alone by a senior officer present during evolutions or
drills, when it commands ⟦ldquo⟧Silence.⟦rdquo⟧ <it>(c)</it> Over a
signal number, when it refers to the signal number of an officer in the
Annual Navy Register.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Convulse</ent>⟦br⟧
